events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 23 points, Anthony Davis had 21 points and 12 rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Toronto Raptors 128-111 on Tuesday night for their seventh win in eight games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 23 points as Lakers win for 7th time in 8 games, beat slumping Raptors 128-111

headlines.description: — Corey Kispert scored 27 points and Deni Avdija added 23 to help the Washington Wizards beat the Milwaukee Bucks 117-113 on Tuesday night despite Giannis Antetokounmpo's triple-double.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards overcome Antetokounmpo's triple-double in a 117-113 victory over the Bucks

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid put Philadelphia ahead with four free throws in the final 40 seconds and finished with 24 points in his first game in nine weeks following knee surgery, leading the 76ers to a 109-105 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 24 points in his return from knee surgery. Sixers top Thunder 109-105

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier picked a great time for his highest-scoring game with the Miami Heat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier scores 34 with eight 3s, Miami holds off New York 109-99 to improve East playoff outlook

headlines.description: — Naz Reid strengthened his case for the Sixth Man of the Year Award with 25 points and six rebounds, Anthony Edwards scored 19 points and the Timberwolves kept up their push for the No. 1 seed in the Western Conference with a 113-106 victory over the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Naz Reid helps Wolves gain ground in West with 113-106 win over Rockets

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Chalk this one up to Nikola Jokic after Victor Wembanyama came up just short of outdueling the player who is hoping to soon pick up his third MVP award.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores 42 and outduels Victor Wembanyama in Nuggets' 110-105 win over Spurs

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 26 points and Jarrett Allen had 21 points and 12 rebounds, helping the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Utah Jazz 129-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Caris LeVert scores 26, leads Cavaliers to 129-113 victory over Jazz

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 22 points, 20 rebounds and nine assists, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Los Angeles Clippers 109-95 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has 22 points, 20 rebounds as Kings beat Clippers 109-95

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 23 points and the Golden State Warriors overcame Luka Doncic's 20th triple-double of the season to beat Dallas 104-100 on Tuesday night, snapping the Mavericks' seven-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors overcome triple-double by Luka Doncic to beat Mavericks 104-100
